{
  "texts": [
    "Gligoric et al. (2024) argues that the use of words to convey a speaker's intent is traditionally distinguished from the mention of words for quoting or describing their properties.",
    "This distinction is pivotal for our research, as translation further complicates this issue.",
    "In our study, Gemini is not prompted to generate 'harmful' language, but with translating it.",
    "Whether translation constitutes a case of mention remains debatable.",
    "However, it is indisputable that translation shares similarities with the act of mentioning."
  ]
}